if you're like most athletes, your muscular tightness is beyond what a conventional foam roller can cure. using harder rollers or pvc pipe isn't enough, because their inflexible surfaces don't work well around bones nor get close enough to muscle attachments. you need more advanced tools that go deeper into the muscle to confront the origin of your pain.

rumbleroller's patented massage tools incorporate the perfect mix of shape, firmness, and resiliency. their effectiveness is legendary, as is their durability and our unwavering commitment to customer satisfaction. if you're serious about feeling and performing better, you owe it to yourself to try rumbleroller.

with very firm but flexible bumps, this model comes closest to mimicking thumb pressure. great for all body parts, and works better around bony areas. recommended for both beginners and experienced users.

  • sizing options
sizing options

rumblerollers are available in three different sizes, and all have the same feel due to their identical bump size and spacing.

before buying your rumbleroller, consider how and where it will be used. if your roller will be kept at one location such as your home or gym, buy the longest one you can afford. its extra length will allow you to do more types of movements and transition more easily between movements. if you travel with your roller, choose one that's small enough to pack and carry.

full-size
6" dia x 31" long (150 x 790mm)
the ultimate deep-tissue roller for gyms and professional users.

midsize
5.5" dia x 22" long (140 x 550mm)
long enough to roll your full back or both legs at once, but less costly and easier to store than the full-size.

compact
5" dia x 13" long (125 x 330mm)
perfect for travel - fits inside most gym bags and suitcases.

premium features on the lx9 include arched base and boarding platform for easier mounting and dismounting, traction handles and grip-and-stretch handholds for a deeper stretch at any angle, and the ez-angle tether that allows you to pre-set your inversion angle to 20, 40 or 60 degrees. the included lumbar bridge and acupressure nodes add targeted traction and pressure-point relief for boosted benefits.

the smooth, firm flextech bed is designed to elongate your spine better than other inversion tables for a better stretch and superior pain relief. the deluxe ez-reach ankle lock system features an extra-long handle to reduce bend and strain and make locking in easier than ever, with micro-adjustments for a customized fit around the ankles. ergo-embrace ankle supports are designed to wrap around the entire ankle and distribute pressure for enhanced comfort and support.

thumb - used mostly for trigger points and the lower back.

cone - used mostly for pinpoint muscle treatment, including the hands and feet.

features

customizable relief - comes with two inserts that easily swap out for the other depending on the desired type of support.

relieve tension headaches - suboccipital muscles, which are located at the base of the skull, control the turning and tilting of the neck. when tense, they can refer to pain throughout the head and neck, often resulting in tension headaches. the textured rubber insert applies firm pressure directly to these trigger points, which will initially feel tender but eventually relax after several minutes for reduced pain and tension.

versatile use – use as a standalone self-massage tool or easily attach to your teeter inversion table with the hook & loop straps for added neck support and tension relief at virtually any angle.

rotating base - the patented swivel feature allows for optimal positioning and side-to-side pressure to enhance the decompression and massage. the steel roller bearing system delivers the smoothest rotation for ease of use and comfort.

cryotherapy - rubber insert can be removed and chilled in the freezer for a therapeutic cooling sensation.
